\title{Perfect field}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-22}
\taxon{definition}

\p{A field #{\FF} is called \define{Perfect} if every irreducible #{p(x)\in\FF[x]} is [seperable](nt-0025).}

\p{\textbf{Exercise:} Prove or find a counter-example: Fields of characteristic zero are perfect.}

\p{\textbf{Puzzle:} Are there any finite fields which are perfect?}
